  "title": "Technician",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Technician – Job Advertisement</strong></h3><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ol><li><p>Prepare and compile technical reports for customers.</p></li><li><p>Update and maintain electrical load lists for power and lighting systems.</p></li><li><p>Complete and manage regulatory documentation related to safety compliance.</p></li><li><p>Support engineers in monitoring project deliverables and proactively provide technical input when required.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate and liaise with relevant parties for the review and checking of drawings.</p></li><li><p>Attend site meetings with owners, consultants, and main contractors to address project operations and coordination matters.</p></li><li><p>Provide technical advice and assistance to the project team, including support during commissioning and servicing activities.</p></li></ol><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ol><li><p>Minimum Diploma in Civil Engineering or equivalent qualification.</p></li><li><p>At least three (4) years of relevant working experience.</p></li><li><p>Willingness to work day or night shifts when required.</p></li><li><p>Availability to work on weekends and public holidays if necessary.</p></li><li><p>Able to respond and work at any time during emergency situations.</p></li></ol>",
